<title>GERMANY: Waigel vows to resist softening EMU criteria.</title>
<headline>Waigel vows to resist softening EMU criteria.</headline>
<dateline>BONN 1996-09-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>German Finance Minister Theo Waigel said on Wednesday he would challenge any efforts within the European Union to weaken the fiscal criteria for Economic and Monetary Union (EMU).</p>
<p>&quot;I will resist any attempts to soften the EMU criteria,&quot; Waigel said in a speech in Bonn.</p>
<p>Waigel also said that financial markets would &quot;immediately punish&quot; any uncertainty about the criteria.</p>
<p>In order to participate in EMU in 1999, EU members in 1997 must show that budget deficits do not exceed three percent of gross domestic product and public debt cannot exceed 60 percent of GDP.</p>
<p>-- Bonn Newsroom, 49 228 26097150</p>
